title: Space Development Agency’s first launch slips due to supply chain setbacks
summary: The first launch of the Space Development Agency’s low Earth orbit satellites that had been scheduled for late September is slipping to no earlier than mid-December.

title: SDA slide reveals Tranche 0 optical terminal manufacturers
summary: “I'm going to do competitions for every Tranche, every layer, every time and it's going to be full and open,” Space Development Agency director Derek Tournear said. “The only way we can do that is if I make sure all the satellites work together as a network."

title: Space Development Agency still hoping to launch satellites next month, ‘but there’s risk’
summary: The Space Development Agency remains optimistic it will launch next month the first satellites of a planned mesh network of sensors and communications nodes in low Earth orbit

title: Space Development Agency’s first launch slips to March due to satellite glitch
summary: The first launch of the Space Development Agency’s constellation planned for mid-December will slip to March 2023 due to an anomaly detected in York Space’s satellites.

title: SpaceX ready for launch with initial satellites for Space Development Agency
summary: SpaceX is now scheduled to launch a batch of 10 communications and missile tracking satellites on the Tranche 0 Flight 1 mission for the Space Development Agency (SDA) on Sunday, April 2, 2023, at 7:29 AM PDT (14:29 UTC). A first attempt on Thursday was aborted at T-3 seconds.
